    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the research and the implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan: `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\n**6 files to modify** following the exact pattern of `Bun.TOML` / `Bun.JSON5`.\n\n### New file: `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`\nA self-contained INI parser/stringifier (no import of the internal `.npmrc` parser). Modeled on `JSON5Object.zig` (both `parse` + `stringify`):\n- **`parse()`**: Iterates lines, handles `[section]` headers, `key = value` pairs, `; #` comments → builds a nested `JSValue` object directly using `putMayBeIndex()`\n- **`stringify()`**: Two-pass output using `wtf.StringBuilder` — top-level primitives as `key = value\\n`, then objects as `[section]\\nkey = value\\n` blocks\n\n### Wiring changes (mechanical, same pattern repeated for each existing format):\n1. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — add lazy callback, `@export`, getter function `getINIObject`, and `const INIObject` import (4 small additions near existing TOML/JSONC/JSON5/YAML entries)\n3. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — add `macro(INI) \\` between `Glob` and `JSON5` (alphabetical)\n4. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to `bunObjectTable`\n5. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — add `namespace INI` with JSDoc before `namespace TOML`",
